# Status Message Template

**MANDATORY:** All agents **MUST** post status updates using this template to ensure consistent, scan-friendly progress communication.

## When to Post Status Messages

Post status messages in the **ticket thread/chat running log** at these times:

- **On start** — When beginning work on a ticket
- **After each meaningful milestone** — After completing significant steps (e.g., "Implemented feature X", "Fixed bug Y", "Completed code review")
- **When blocked** — Immediately when encountering blockers or dependencies
- **On completion** — When work is finished (before moving ticket to next column)

**Frequency:** Post updates at least once per meaningful milestone. For long-running work, post updates every 30-60 minutes or after each major step.

## Where to Post

- **Ticket thread/chat running log** — Post status messages in the active conversation/chat where the ticket work is being discussed
- **Do NOT** post status messages in artifact bodies (artifacts are for structured documentation, not real-time updates)

## Status Message Template (Copy-Paste)

```markdown
## Status Update

**Context:** [Brief context: what ticket/feature you're working on]

**State:** [Current state: Starting / In progress / Blocked / Done]

**What I did:**
- [Bullet point of completed work]
- [Another bullet point if applicable]

**Next:**
- [What you're doing next]
- [Next steps]

**Risks:** [Any blockers, dependencies, or concerns. Use "None" if no risks]

**ETA:** [Estimated time to completion or next milestone. Use "Unknown" if uncertain]

**Links:** [Relevant links: PRs, artifacts, docs. Use "None" if no links]
```

